title: Russian supply ship docks at space station - The Republic
text:
An unmanned Russian cargo ship has docked with the International Space Station, bringing the astronauts aboard 2.3 tons of supplies ranging from air to garlic. The Progress M-29M spacecraft blasted off from Russia's space launch complex in Baikonur, Kazakhstan, on Thursday night docked with the space station shortly before 2 a.m. Moscow time Friday .
 The Republic.
